Practical 1 : To create a Virtual Machine and set up a basic server on AWS using both Windows and Linux operating systems.
Procedure:
Open the AWS Management Console and search for EC2 in the search bar.

Click on Instances from the EC2 dashboard.

Select Launch Instance and provide the required details.

Enter the instance name as ExamServer.

Under Quick Start, select Windows as the operating system.

Click on Create New Key Pair and provide the following details:

Name: Exam123

Key Pair Type: RSA

Private Key File Format: .pem

Click Create to generate the key pair.

After creating the key pair, click on Launch Instance.

Refresh the page or navigate back to the Instances section.

Select the created instance and click on Connect.

Under the RDP Client tab, click on Download Remote Desktop File.

Next, click on Get Password.

Upload the previously downloaded .pem private key file and click on Decrypt Password.

Copy the generated password and save it for future reference.

To access the remote server, open the downloaded Remote Desktop file from downloads.

Click Connect.

Enter the decrypted password obtained earlier.

Click OK, then Yes, to establish the connection and access the remote desktop environment.

Note:
For creating a Red Hat instance, select the Red Hat application during instance creation. All other configuration options can remain the same as used for the Windows instance.
